br.com.gamemods.regionmanipulator

Class CorruptChunk

  • br.com.gamemods.regionmanipulator.CorruptChunk

  • public class CorruptChunk

    This is the same as class Chunk but holding a ByteArray instead of NbtFile because the chunk content could not be parsed.

    The chunk represented here will be raw and unparsed, you will have access to it's NBT data to do any modification as you wish.

    See Also:
    class Chunk, ByteArray

      • CorruptChunk

        public CorruptChunk(@NotNull
                    ChunkPos position,
                    @NotNull
                    java.util.Date lastModified,
                    @Nullable
                    kotlin.Array[] chunkContent,
                    long location,
                    int allocationSize,
                    @Nullable
                    java.lang.Integer length,
                    @Nullable
                    java.lang.Integer compression,
                    @NotNull
                    java.lang.Throwable throwable)

        This is the same as class Chunk but holding a ByteArray instead of NbtFile because the chunk content could not be parsed.

        The chunk represented here will be raw and unparsed, you will have access to it's NBT data to do any modification as you wish.

        Parameters:
        position - The X/Z position in the world where this chunk resides.
        lastModified - The last modification registered in MCA file. It will not be updated automatically.
        chunkContent - The bytes that compounds this chunk. Be aware that it's corrupt.Null if the reader couldn't even reach the chunk's content section in the MCA file.
        location - The position where the chunk is located in the MCA file.
        allocationSize - The amount of data which was allocated to this chunk. The chunk don't need to use all the bytes.
        length - The actual amount of bytes that this chunk is using in it's allocated section. Always less or equals to allocationSize.Null if the reader couldn't read this information from the chunk's body.
        compression - The compression format used to compress the chunk content. 1 for GZIP and 2 for ZIP.Null if the reader couldn't read this information from the chunk's body.
        throwable - The throwable that prevented the chunk from loading.
        See Also:
        class Chunk, ByteArray
